text:
bottle
AROMA: hops in the first place (citrus, flowers, herbs) however somehow repressed, later comes a bit of chocolate, coffee and roastiness;
APPEARANCE: clear black/dark brown, ruby under intensive light, spectacular beige head, no lacing;
TASTE: notes characteristic for Baltic porter hidden under hoppy notes which connotes rather black IPA, unquestionably high sweetness firmly countered by considerable bitterness (very high for Baltic porter);
PALATE: body seems medium, low carbonation, warming from alcohol, finish is quite long, bitter, not astringent;
OVERALL: interesting attempt, but this Baltic porter enriched with aroma introduced by Amarillo etc. doesnt speak to me.
EXPIRATION DATE: 2014-11-20
